8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 1033, L.D. 1575, “An Act to Allow a
10 Legislator to Choose to Be Paid on an Annual Basis”
11 Amend the bill by striking out all of the emergency preamble.
12 Amend the bill in section 1 in the indented paragraph in the 4th line from the end (page
13 2, line 6 in L.D.) by inserting after the following: "that" the following: ', effective January
14 1, 2026,'
15 Amend the bill in section 1 in the indented paragraph in the next to the last line (page
16 2, line 8 in L.D.) by striking out the following: "26" and inserting the following:
17 'approximately'
18 Amend the bill by striking out all of the emergency clause.
19 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
20 number to read consecutively.
21 SUMMARY
2222 This amendment amends the bill by clarifying that a Legislator may choose to be paid
2233 the salary for each year of the biennium to which that Legislator is entitled in approximately
2244 equal payments over that corresponding year of the biennium. The amendment also
2255 removes the emergency preamble and emergency clause.
